This paper deals with the topic of adversarial perturbations in images and videos, which is a common area of research in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural network models for classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential use of the perturbations for image and video compression, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial perturbations, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
